Dear Elves! 
We're having a fundraising Saint Nicholas Day at GODny this Saturday! Make sure you do come and chip in for a decent cause. Alex is very sick and if we don't help @hello_morning_blog and @rawpawattack, he's not gonna make it.
( he suffers from SMA:
Spinal muscular atrophy (SMA) is a genetic disease affecting the part of the nervous system that controls voluntary muscle movement. Most of the nerve cells that control muscles are located in the spinal cord, which accounts for the word spinal in the name of the disease).
His only chase is Onasemnogene abeparvovec, sold under the trade name Zolgensma. It is a gene therapy medication used to treat spinal muscular atrophy. It is used with corticosteroids as a one-time injection into a vein. It was approved in the United States in 2019 for children less than two years old.
So instead of blowing your bobs on shit, pop round between 8.00 and 10.00 with any amount you can spare.
Every little helps!
And spread the word ya'll! .
